                <h4>What is the voting age population of Richwood, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Richwood, West Virginia, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 1,785.  The voting age population is 51.2% male and 48.8% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Richwood, West Virginia residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 24.6% of
                        the residents of Richwood are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Richwood, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Richwood are 94.4% White, 3.7% Two or more races and 1.9% Black. Additionally, 0.7% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Richwood, West Virginia residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Richwood, 32.7% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 60.1%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    20.0% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Richwood.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Richwood, West Virginia residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 45.3% of
                    Richwood residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Richwood, West Virginia residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    85.3% of
                    Richwood residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 13.2%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 3.8%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Richwood, West Virginia residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Richwood residents aged 5 and older, 1.7% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                0.5% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.2% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.0% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Richwood, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Richwood is 17.2%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Richwood, West Virginia residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Richwood, 11.3% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
